-- Rays Sign Ex-Yankees Outfielder Matsui to Minor-League Contract
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 2012-04-30T15:23:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/rays-sign-ex-yankees-outfielder-matsui-to-minor-league-contract.html
The Tampa Bay Rays signed former
New York Yankees outfielder Hideki Matsui to a minor-league
contract,  Major League Baseball  said on its Twitter feed.  Matsui, 37, played for the Oakland Athletics last season,
batting .251 with 12 home runs and 72 runs batted in. He played
for the Yankees for seven years, and was the most valuable
player of the 2009 World Series.  For his major-league career, Matsui has batted .285 with
173 home runs and 753 runs batted in.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  